# Architecture overview (read once before starting)

## What we're building

A Notion-like rich-text editor (block-based, slash menu, drag handle, floating toolbar, markdown shortcuts, code highlight) packaged as a **Web Component** `<notion-editor>`. The editor lives in its own pnpm workspace package and never depends on host business code. The host frontend uses it via **one workspace dep + one ~30-line wrapper component** — nothing else changes in the host.

## Strategy: fork-vendor from `lexical-playground`

[Lexical Playground](https://github.com/facebook/lexical/tree/main/packages/lexical-playground) already implements every feature we need. We **copy its source verbatim** into `src/playground-vendor/` and **never modify** those files. All custom code lives in sibling folders (`src/ui/`, `src/plugins/`, `src/element/`, `src/serializer/`). Lexical upgrades become a folder-replace, not a merge.

