## Isolation contract (every prompt must respect this)

1. The editor package never imports from `frontend/src/**` or `backend/**`. Guarded by ESLint in P9.
2. The host `frontend/src/**` never imports `lexical` or `@lexical/*` directly. Guarded by ESLint in P10. The only entry point is `import { NotionEditor } from "@/components/NotionEditor"`, which itself imports `"@app/lexical-editor"`.
3. `src/playground-vendor/**` is read-only. Adaptations go in `src/plugins/` or `src/ui/`.
4. The Web Component `<notion-editor>` exchanges only `SerializedDocument` JSON — Lexical types do not leak across the shadow boundary.

