### `frontend/packages/lexical-editor/HANDOFF.md`

```markdown
# @app/lexical-editor — hand-off

Notion-like rich-text editor as a Web Component (`<notion-editor>`).
Isolated from host business code by a pnpm workspace boundary plus ESLint guards in both directions.

## How to use in any feature

```

import { NotionEditor, type SerializedDocument } from "@/components/NotionEditor"

function NoteEditor({ note, save }: { note: { content?: SerializedDocument }; save: (c: SerializedDocument) => void }) {

return <NotionEditor value={note.content} onChange={save} />

}

```

## Public API

- Custom element: `<notion-editor>`
- Property: `value: SerializedDocument | null`
- Events: `editor-ready`, `editor-input`, `editor-change` (debounced 400ms)
- `SerializedDocument`, `SerializedBlock`, `BlockType`, `RichSpan` types are exported from `@app/lexical-editor` (re-exported by the host wrapper).

## Local development

    pnpm --filter @app/lexical-editor dev      # http://localhost:5183/
    pnpm --filter @app/lexical-editor test     # vitest
    pnpm --filter @app/lexical-editor test:e2e # playwright
    pnpm --filter @app/lexical-editor build    # produces dist/

## Architecture

- `src/playground-vendor/` — verbatim copy of `facebook/lexical` `lexical-playground/src`. **Never modified.** Upgrade by replacing the folder.
- `src/ui/EditorRoot.tsx` — composes the vendor plugins we use.
- `src/element/NotionEditorElement.ts` — Web Component wrapper, owns the shadow root.
- `src/serializer/{toDocument,fromDocument}.ts` — the only place that knows about both Lexical and `SerializedDocument`.
- `src/plugins/` — our own plugins and any wrapper that adapts a vendor plugin.

## Isolation contract

1. The editor never imports from `frontend/src/**` or `backend/**` (enforced by `frontend/packages/lexical-editor/.eslintrc.cjs`).
2. The host `frontend/src/**` never imports `lexical` / `@lexical/*` directly (enforced by `frontend/.eslintrc.cjs`). Only entry: `@/components/NotionEditor`.
3. Lexical types do not cross the shadow boundary. The Web Component speaks `SerializedDocument` JSON.

## Upgrading Lexical

1. `git clone --depth 1 -b vX.Y.Z https://github.com/facebook/lexical /tmp/lexical-clone`
2. `rm -rf frontend/packages/lexical-editor/src/playground-vendor`
3. `cp -R /tmp/lexical-clone/packages/lexical-playground/src/. frontend/packages/lexical-editor/src/playground-vendor/`
4. Bump `lexical` and `@lexical/*` versions in `frontend/packages/lexical-editor/package.json` to match.
5. `pnpm install && pnpm --filter @app/lexical-editor dev` — verify slash/drag/toolbar.
6. Fix breakages in `EditorRoot.tsx` or by adding wrappers in `src/plugins/`. **Never modify `playground-vendor/`.**
